text: Hidden gem. Quiet, cozy, great place to work or just think. Has those leave an anonymous story boxes. Highly recommended. $6 for a delicious crepe, salad and big coffee.
Strawberry dark chocolate crepe was awesome! Crepe was a chewy texture and cooked just right. Cappuccino was decent :) super cute decor and chill music.
Get a Nutella cr√™pe, some jasmine tea, seat back, relax & enjoy their playlist of jazz divas (Ella Fitzgerald, Carla Bruni,...)
This is such a great hidden gem. Great place to work because no one knows about it yet!
Quiet, great crepes and tea. Perfect place to relax, read a book or study.
Definitely a hidden gem. Fun drinks menu and the crepes are delish.
It's true, this place is a hidden gem. Love the savoury cr√™pes, especially the meat lover.
Try the terimayo crepe. Really yummy. One of these days I'll try a different one, but so far, I can't escape this one. :-)
Great vibe for conversation, coffee, reading, relaxing and eating some crepes
Breakfast specials (ham/cheese + egg crepe, salad, tea/coffee) for $6!
Best service ever. Always happy when I walk out of this branch location:)
VanCity!!
Definitely the Royal Milk Tea Latte and Almond cheesecake. They also gave customers a small cheesecake treat to commemorate the Cafe's anniversary :) great service, with jazz music to boot!
Great food. Great drinks. Very unique menu. Don't listen to the reviews praising the Royal Milk Tea Latte. Its just a tea latte with honey. Not special. Their other drinks are great!
So excellent.  It is a cozy cute caf√©.  We went for breakfast and the food and service was great. I had a lavender tea latte that was so yummy
I had the mini breakfast with half a waffle, and absolutely LOVED it. Great portions to give you a taste of everything
Eggs Benny with smoked salmon on hashbrowns with a lavender tea latt√© - deliciousüëå lovely atmosphere too!
Fun little cafe with western and traditional breakfasts. Definitely a favorite.
Cute little Japanese cafe serves excellent lattes and all day breakfast! Try the eggs benny with smoked salmon.. The eggs are cooked to perfect soft, yolky perfection!
Get the okonomiyaki pancake (split if in a group) and a royal milk tea. Surprisingly good greasy hash browns too.
Loved the atmosphere here. I got the cheesy omurice with tomato mushroom sauce and it was absolutely amazing.
This is one of a kind Japanese style brunch cafe. Perfect for autumn. Try Omu Rice.
Alina is the way to go!
Ask for Amber! She's an amazing stylist !
Devon does an amazing head of hair!
Breanne is amazing!!!
The food was excellent! XLB and vinegar was slightly sweet. Very different but tasty.  The hand pulled noodles were good, and I definitely recommend the beef rolls.
Awesome thinly wrapped XLB and amazing honey garlic spareribs. Everything here tastes fantastic even though the dishes can't be very healthy haha
watch it on diners, drive-ins, and dives, then order the demo'd beef roll, lamb cumin noodles, & fried pork dumplings, plus the spicy ginger beef.
It's super busy here so it took them a long time to take my order. But everything turned out to be worth the waiting. Absolutely genuine Northern Chinese food, tastes so good!
Love this place. My favorite is the Beijing noodles and the beef and green onions. Personally think the beef roll is over rated   the hoisin sauce drowns out all the other flavors.
The spicy cilantro salad, spicy cucumber dish and spicy fish with cilantro stew
Every thing is so good. Try the spicy cucumber, potato roll or Dan Dan noodle.
You walk in wondering why everyone's so quiet - then you eat & realize it's bc the food is INSANE. the beef roll is crazy good
Beef roll is pretty good! However, service was slow during rush hour, friend waited almost half hour for his bowl of noodles because they ran out and had to make more. Don't forget xpect discounts!
Amazingly fresh and tasty northern Chinese cuisine. Try the chicken & noodle cold appetizer and grab ANY noodle w broth. Swoon.
The corn tortillas were some of the best I've had so far. You can't go wrong with either the meat or vegetable tacos. Both wonderfully flavorful and creative!
La Taqueria Taco Shop was featured in You Gotta Eat Here Season 2 Episode 21. Great tacos! You can never go wrong. However, I think they are moving to a new location because the building is changing.
These tacos are likely the only real Mexican food in Vancouver. The lineup can be out the door and around the corner but they're worth it. I recommend pairing your tacos with a Guava soda. üëç
The tacos are amazing, the quesadillas are fantastic, nachos are wonderful, sopes are also delicious! Great cocktail menu, too. Note that alcohol can only be consumed indoors.
A Texan visiting Vancouver heard about good tacos and said "We'll see..."  SERIOUSLY good tacos.  Not just good for Vancouver, but they could stand on their own anywhere.
Amazin little spot for fresh made tacos (small size) order about 4 or more to fill you up. Great food though #fresh #handmade #mexicana #Canada
most authentic Mexican tacos I've ever tasted. These are the closest things you'll get to real deal Mexican street tacos, I suggest you try the rajas con crema!!
All their tacos taste amazing, especially the Carnitas and Tinga de Pollo. The staff is very friendly as well.
Everything is great here. Their Tacos are like heaven in your mouth. Pricey but justified. Always busy. This place must be making a fortune!!
Best tacos you can hace un Vancouver. You must try Pastor and Barbacoa. To drink, the Horchata is amazing.
Everything is fresh, I can always count on Whole Foods to have any kind of healthy and organic ingredients I might need, whether it iscooking & other lifestyle items.
Whole Foods reimburses parking tickets dispensed displaying the green stripe only -- those machines are located next to the entrance.
I'm all about the 2 for $6 prepared foods for a grab and go lunch! Hit the juice bar for some fresh pressed goodness: Cool Ruby with some kale should do the trick!
If you drive & park in the parkade, be sure to buy your ticket from machine next to whole foods doors, or else they won't reimburse your $2. (London Drugs doesn't reimburse either)
GMO's sold here.  But the best?  Saying that the pineapples from Costa Rica are pesticide free.  Not.  I live there and the amounts of chemicals used are astounding.
If you're in the mood for soup, walk on over to the seafood bar instead of the salad bar. Their prices and soup quality are better!
Make sure you use the compost - the extra few seconds it takes to do it right (hopefully I did it right!) is a great step in the right direction :)
The lemon cake is life-changing! 3 words: cream cheese frosting. Need I say more?
Great range and informed service. Not the cheapest, but I feel it is worth it. Utter quality!
Vegan chocolate parfaits are the best things I've ever tasted... Heaven in a cup
Fresh fish from today‚Äôs morning. Delicious nigiri.
Sushi donut
Easy way to freshen up the look of your living room is to change the accent pillows. HomeSense has a huge selection for many new looks!
Gourmet kitchen area has some great treats and finds. :)
It has a paid ticketed parking garage
The #pb protein is pretty delicious.
Super hip spot with amazing veggie and vegan food. Great drinks, nice staff, and an awesome vibe!
I'm not vegan so was surprised how flavorful and nicely prepared the food is.
I love having such flavorful vegan food!  We had butter chicken and it was an amazing dish tastes like an Indian curry.
It was delicious (I particularly loved my cashew cheesecake) and I will definitely go back, but overall the food was quite simple for the price.
Great fries, especially the chilly cheese.
Super good. All veggie but feels like bar food
The Peach Pekoe Iced tea is great!
Mac&Cheese
Get The Macro bowl
If you love ice cream then this is the place to come to . You get to see how the ice cream is made and the different toppings. It is best to have it on a stick not a cup and have Creme Brulee.
Definitely a bit pricey for ice cream but still worth trying, especially the torched creme br√ªl√©e liquid nitrogen ice cream.
Double Oreo is my favourite, but if you get s'mores they toast the marshmallow in front of you. Maybe not the best ice cream in the city but a really cool experience.
Loved the creme brulee ice cream sandwhich. Will go back to other ones. Be warned long lineups are common, so show up early or during the week vs weekend.
Liquid nitrogen, so you know the ice cream is fresh. Get the Irish coffee, it's a perfect way to cool down.
The lemon froyo is killer and the creme br√ªl√©e is to die for
Very good quality ice cream, hand mixed to order. Yes, expensive but still value for money.
Delicious fresh made ice cream with liquid nitrogen! SO GOOD!
Creme br√ªl√©e ice cream to die for! Love this place.
Had the Creme Br√ªl√©e! It was awesome.
Four cheese mushroom is great,side dishes like sausage is also highly recommended. Make sure to call or make reservation before come in. Always so busy
Pulled pork poutine and a juicy slab of pork chop with heaps of tasty lard - they‚Äôre called the flying pig for a reason!
Get the bone marrow cheesy bread! The salmon platter was pretty good too. The walnut old fashion was not my fav‚Äîa little too thick with the maple syrup. Great vibe.

Salt and pepper squid was good, but know that it also has jalape√±o peppers ‚Äî which is not mentioned on the menu, so I was a little surprised by how spicy they were. Lips were numb. Good, but spicy.
Get whatever platter special they have. Usually around $35/pp and it's 4-5 courses of food. Best deal. Really high quality. Bone marrow, steak, fish, shrimp/lobster rissotto, etc
Amazing pork chop and fries with pulled pork.  A must visit.  Also directly across from several great next stops on you way through Yale Town.
In all my years I've never been here and I feel bad. This place is awesome. Awesome food awesome prices and awesome interior. Great for groups and family. HIGHLY recommended!
Fun atmosphere + great food makes this place one of the best places to go for  dinner in Yaletown. Get the halibut with gnocchi and add a side of brussel sprouts-- you won't be disappointed.
Caprese salad was worse than home & the steak was cut the wrong way across the grain. The cauliflower on the share plate was awesome & the Arctic char was great. Just cant forgive the steak.
Corned beef hash was very good as is the free banana bread! Great place for brunch and we didn't have a wait around 11am on Saturday.
This place has amazing service and it has the best selection of hats in Vancouver by far!
The staff is super nice. Bought myself an awesome hat.
The staff is super nice. Bought an awesome hat.
Great after-sales support, this San Fran import has great product.
If you're in the mood for Ishi-Yaki (hot stone cooking right at the table),  but not in the mood for meat, try the Kinoko Meshi. Hot stone bowl rice, mixed mushrooms, and iwanori, mixed tableside.
Their happy hour is pretty good!  Their host and servers are awesome.  Servers can be catty in Yaletown but the girls here are awesome!  Forget about the Flying Pig across the street!
Jumbo Seared Scallops (market price daily) with a to-die-for mushroom & balsamic reduction sauce...... MUST TRY!!
Try the Hello Kitty Cocktail as well as the Pineapple martini. For food, Chicken Karaage, Negitoro and Ishiyaki stone bowl
For dinner, make sure to try the mushroom stone bowl (kinoko meshi). Also, if available, the matcha brulee daily special is excellent!
Their Hapa Hour now not only includes cheap food, but also cheap alcohol. Go from 5-6 to try it out.
Their lettuce wraps are very tasty. Try the hello kitty drink *hic*
Wasn't happy they didn't tell us the 1/2 off hapas didnt include all the hapas so tht kinda ruined the experience but food was great esp gindara, ebi mayo, aburi saba! Tuna carpaccio tasted weird tho
If you're here alone, ask for the tasting menu- 3 items for $12. It's like tapas for 1.
Great food. Weird vibe: rap music and sports on the TVs...
For that day a vegan wants to go wild :P, not the healthiest but man is it delicious and it's also a really cool place to go to with your non vegan friends as it never fails to amuse
Pretty good. Friendly folks. I had the gluten free mushroom burger because their regular patties are the ones that taste like beef and I'm not into that.
Awesome vegan food truck where the idea is to convert neat eaters into vegan lovers! Oily food, but it's worth it. (4 of 4 petals via Fondu)
Absolutely fantastic food, you can't even tell it is entirely vegan!
One of the best vegetarian places in the city!
Vegan chicken burger!
Vegan http://www.happycow.net/north_america/canada/british_columbia/vancouver/
Salmon Oshi Sushi and Ebi Oshi Sushi are the best. The Minami Zen box is great value and includes two of the Salmon Oshi Sushi. You can also order half orders of the sushi and rolls.

Loved the sushi √† la carte, decently priced, fresh and creative. Happy hour on Thursdays from 3-6 consists of $10 for a pint of Asahi beer & a plate of gyozas. Cool and crisp ambiance for trendy crowd

Tried their 3 course Minami set, starts with a 7 pieces sushi selection, entree of sable fish and beef tenderloin, finished with green tea ice cream and cake.  All for $60, great deal!! All yummy too.
Sooo good! The sushi are amazing and I just love how tasty the kaisen soba pepperoncino tasted! They carry a more simple menu for afternoons! If you wanna have all options go for dinner!
Not a sushi fan ?? Try this restaurant! You will fall in love with sushi.. Staff were amazing! Beside sushi order the prawn! It was incredibly delicious!
We learned a lot about sake while enjoying the delicious tasting course. If you're looking to go for drinks afterwards this restaurant is very well located with loads of bars on the same street.
The salmon oshi and mackerel oshi are to die. The salmon oshi is buttery with a jalape√±o kick. For those of you that love mackerel, the oshi has a perfect balance between smoky and salty flavors.
Amazing sushi selection! Excellent service. It's a fancy dinner restaurant, that's why it's pricier than a regular sushi place. The green tea cake was very good as well.

Supposedly a high end Japanese restaurant, great service, prices are not cheap, portions r small and they taste decent. Not the best value if you ask me, but it's decent and has great decor/atmosphere
Doesn't matter what food you order @Minami everything tastes so delicious. We had octopus,  pork trio, aburi sushi..Couldn't get enough of it.
Seriously one of the most inspirational home stores in Canada. It's one of my fave stops in Vancouver.
If you like fancy home stuff they def have it here :) great place for gifts.
The items are so delicate and unique
Home decor shopping heaven! Also fabulous gifts for showers, weddings, etc
I learned today that they have a website and they ship! One big pb solved.
Best place to do some Christmas shopping!
I love this store. Truly.
#1 place for engagement gift shopping!
Home and vintage decor shopping heaven!
The prettiest place in town! xo

Before u know it, u be poppin oysters like candy (be warned, they‚Äôre $3++ per shell). There are at least 6 diff sauces to go with them as well. The vibe‚Äôs awesome, energy on a fri night is on point
Cool little place, good for drinks and shareable food. Everything I had was good, can't beat the Canadian service, everybody is nice, decent prizes. Do recommend.
Amazing HH! ! 1.50 oysters and they even have it on Saturdays. Service is great and they have a decent wine and beer selection too. Wish I lived here so I could keep coming back!

Sit at the bar cause the bartenders and shucksters (made this up) are hilarious and fun. Great variety of oysters, though pricey. The lobster poutine was good too. Like the variety of homemade sauces.
The potato crusted halibut was absolutely amazing the seafood pasta was delicious and we shared the oyster Rockefeller which was divine
This place is happening. Great food all around, friendly people and a nice vibe. You're in Vancouver so you're going to have seafood. This is the place to do it.
The ceasers !! Make sure you order one ! and the oysters are awesome .

Damnit! Came too full for the happy hour specials. Oyster prices comparable to other oyster places that are high quality. The sauces, particularly the first two and last one (habanero, so go easy) +++
ALWAYS a blast. Go to Yaletown location over Gastown! Fun music, happy hour, and the servers cute! Go with girlfriends - don‚Äôt go with a date!
Always a fun night out. Fun servers, delicious careers and fresh seafood. Definitely get the oysters and the prawn cocktail, yum!
Love this place. It‚Äôs been around for a long time. Real authentic straight up Mexican food. They have great lunch special menu!
Try the carne asada Mexican dish with guac and chips! Don't forget the mandarin soda!
They have a second, smaller, original location a few doors west of the larger dining location. The sign says "take out", but thy have a few tables and the service is fast.
The Enchilada with Avocado Lunch Special is a good option. Vegetarians can ask for cheese (veggies?) instead of chicken.
Order the Limonade...refreshing, tangy, and full of lime-yumminess!  I order mine half fizzy, half flat for extra smooth flavour...
One of the best tacos I've had in North America! Great prices, too. Fresh food and fantastic service.
The menudo soup is the best! And the lemonade. You should try
Everything here it's so good! Try the azteca soup and burrito or the green enchiladas!!!
Authentic and spectacular !    Hand made margs are the bomb and the owner and staff are a delight
The Azteca soups is good, and is really close to Mexican food say it a Mexican!
Chambar is now open for brunch with ~300 seats. The menu is essentially the same as the Cafe Medina menu of old (including waffles). So if you're looking to skip Medina's crazy lines...
Great patio. Probably the best mussels in Vancouver. Never had a bad meal here. The staff are always friendly & helpful. Menu changes seasonally so never becomes boring. Portions are a decent size.
One of the best breakfasts I had in a while. It is crowded, be ready to wait in line and to pay top dollar, place is  it cheap. But it is worth it.
Great place, one of the best brunches I've ever had. Place is crowded so be prepared to wait in line, it is not cheap but is well worth it.
The salmon waffle was really nice. My brother had the steak and eggs and I was super jealous. I thought it would be huge but actually it‚Äôs a nice brunch portion. Strong recommend.
We just dropped in for coffee and waffles this trip. On a previous visit we had a great meal in the restaurant. Friendly and helpful staff and a great atmosphere.
Steak and eggs were very good! Maybe make a reservation if you want a table for brunch at the weekend
Great place for brunch or for any meal. Healthy and delicious. Casual yet sort of upscale, but more casual.
Very fresh and delicious dishes prepared with organic ingredient tasting so fresh you would want seconds! Try the miso glazed tuna for lunch üëåüèº
The menu effortlessly hops from BC-flavoured French classics to Belgian moules-frites. Also known for serving the city's best tajine. [Eater 38 Member]
Never order the large Charlie unless sharing with the whole table, most servers will discourage it! It comes in a large serving bowl
Amazing food. Get Charlie Bowl and you can have sweet + savory. The biscuits you can pour syrup on. Decor was pretty IKEA Hipster. Also, major turn off that they get their coffee from...JJ Bean? Wtf?
Portions are HUGE- ordered the small Charlie and couldn't finish it. The wait for a table is quite long on weekends/holidays.
Definitely try out the gravy coop. Huge portion. Biscuits crisp af. Chicken tender and juicy. Best brunch I've had for a while. Go with a huge appetite.
We were advised it was a 45 minute wait but it ended up being 30 minutes. Definitely worth it. Tried the chorizo benedict, sugared bacon and pancakes. Everything was great.
Very long line (1+ hour) but worth the wait. By God, the eggs Benedict are really, really good. The huevos rancheros are amazing too. Service was 10/10.
Generous portions! The gravy coop and single pancake (side) is more than enough for two people to share.
Pulled pork Benny is a strong contender for ‚Äúif you had a last meal request...‚Äùü§§ Hearty veggie bowl got a thumbs up, too.‚úîÔ∏è
I was told to try a Ceaser. An acquired taste for sure but  made and presented. The breakfast was outstanding.
Wowwww everything is good I recommend cinnamon Bun Pancakes, toooo nice  Chicken French Toast, Fried Chicken & waffle so good üòä
Nice place for pizza and pasta. It‚Äôs a great place to bring children as the many board games will keep them occupied. üò¨ Tip: make a reservation!
Delicious! Pick out a game as soon as you get there & enjoy the time to relax & have fun. It's definitely a great meal experience...would even be great for little ones there are all types of games!
Cozy place with delicious pizza. Really enjoyed playing a game while waiting. The ham and cheese platter was great as appetizer, the half size was good for 4 people. We had 2 pizzas for 4 adults.
Great spot for playing board games with friends while enjoying a pizza. I liked the Agricola. If you don't know what to play there will be someone there to help you choose a game.
Loved the (somewhat) retro Italian pizza place vibe. Lots of board games and an extensive menu üòã
They have Cards Against Humanity and the Bigger Blacker Box! Super friendly staff and good options to nom on whilst playing board games.
They have amazing pizza and board games are great add on. Sometimes they get really pizza so call in advance if you want a table
Board games and great food,  woo hoo.   The cocktail list was not stellar but did have a lot of classics on it.
The meat lover pizza is very good. Great staff, someone teaches you how to play the board games!
The cheese pizza is so good, and all of the slices are pretty affordable
Great selection of drinks and snacks (at concession prices: $5 for popcorn), no tipping, and credit/debit only- no cash!!
Great venue for theatre, smaller concerts etc,
If you are using the east parking lot leave lots of time for the cluster muck that occurs at the ridiculous parking pay stations. 15-20 min wait to pay for busy events.
Print out your ticket ahead of time to save you the trouble! I thought they were Eco-friendly but since my tickets were purchased by my aunt, I had to print it elsewhere myself.
Pre order for intermission, so your drinks will be waiting for you.
Did you know you can pre-order your drinks for intermission? No line-ups!
Small old seats, not great if you are tall, also sucks if the person in front of you is taller than five feet
A very clean and well-maintained establishment. The entrance at the south corner typically has shorter lines. The same can be said for the bars on the 2nd floor, though they offer less drink options.
upcoming events... Queen Elizabeth Theatre Queen Elizabeth Theatre vancouver
Buy tickets at a discount starting at noon the day of a show
I agree accept debit or credit please!
Visit Fat Duck truck!
Yes! Take debit or credit! So annoying.

Arena is in Vancouver's Chinatown. Eat at the Wiser Center Ice Grill. The Skytrain stops outside of the stadium. If you need help deciding which Seats to purchase for your next Canucks game, check out
The highlight of the gold medal memory for me was either the breakout of the bar united in singing Oh Canada, or the beautiful sounds of car horns which overtook the country for hours after the win
In 2007, one of the best rock reunions ever happened when The Police decided to tour again. After nearly 21 years apart, the guys came together for a massive tour, starting at Rogers Arena.
The arena tour is well worth it; you'll see a lot of cool places you wouldn't normally have access to.
This indoor sports arena is where you'll catch entertainment shows and sports events. Go on a Rogers Arena tour if you wish to learn about important and historical events that took place here.
Love the team members here and management. So friendly and upbeat, right down to security and the 50/50 ticket folks and hosts.
Here for a concert? Remember that once the headliners hit the stage beer sales end. Make sure to grab them before that and enjoy the show!
A very very good and a very very cool and big arena and the home arena of my favorite NHL team the Vancouver Canucks and I have seen good concerts there like Metallica.
The Pint Public House is a great spot for after the Game. Plenty of seating and awesome weeknight specials
Good sight lines from everywhere - pricey tickets though. Get your food early is the best option if you don‚Äôt want to run out of food
Try the mix grill platter. A tasty combination of lamb, chicken and falafel ...  Mix in rice, Greek salad and some bread and you got yourself a hearty meal. It's a solid go.
The Einstein platter is so delicious and amazing portion/value for what you pay. 1 huge meal for me but 2 meals for most.
Lamb shank platter for $12.99 (2019)! It‚Äôs crazy cheap, and tastes amazing! My daughter loves their donair/wrap, too! üëçüèº
Best shawarma joint I've tried so far on the downtown east side. The lamb shank is a big hit with my co-workers.
Best Shawarmas in the city at a ridiculously great price!
Best Lamb wraps And fabulous friendly service!
Awesome lamb shank platter.
Wonderful service.
This is really not good... Please dont waste your money. There are cheaper and nicer things in life.
Great selection of board games, and there are play tables in the back.  Prices are a bit high
Great place to buy board games!! Also play & try out new games every Wednesday & Sunday :) - Maureen www.MaureenSeguin.com
Amazing service here - the clerks are super knowledgable! Get Hanabi.
Great selection, fair prices, knowledgeable staff and play tables!

Feast on free-range egg benedicts and definitely try the double-smoked bacon. Chicken and waffles fans are in for a treat thanks to guilt-free organic birds. The long queues aren't putting people off.
We were excited to find this place and the food was wonderful. Potato skewers were delightful. The egg sandwich with arugula, mushrooms and hollandaise sauce was crazy good. A bit of a messy meal.
Half a waffle and a piece a chicken for $11.75. What a rip off! But it was pretty tasty. The truffle lemon potato skewers was really good too. This place seems like a copy of The Big Egg in Portland.
Traditional breakfast items with unique and fresh ingredients. Excellent! You'll come back again and again. Try the lemon truffle oil skewer with your breaky
I was warned by the beautiful Laura at the window that the egg in my sandwich might explode as it was soft poached. "Explode?" I said, incredulous. "Yes," she answered, smiling. She wasn't wrong.
Went there for the first time the other day and had the Double Smoked Bacon on a Ciabatta. It was delicious!
Chicken and waffles offered on Fridays and most weekends I believe is to die for
Excellent hash brown skewer. And I love it when Anne Hathaway serves me breakfast.
Truffle lemon potato skewers. Get them.
Try the pancakes. They blew my mind.
There's a lot to try, and all of it is good! I especially enjoyed their zucchini lime cake (not sure of the exact name though)
Very tasteful interior, huge variety of baked goods to choose from, and friendly staff.
Run here!! You will need the calorie burn before you embark on all of the yummy pastries, cakes and breads this place has!!
Amazing pastries and cakes, highly recommend the savoury scones
The variety of the pastries are what makes it unique...has few sears so not a spot to sit and work!
Absolutely everything is good here! You'll just have to come for multiple visits just to try everything. The sugar buns are off the wall.
Amazing service and the flourless brownie was beyond delicious. Cool place with great atmosphere!
Though their sweet breads are delicious, their savoury selection is worth trying as well.
Everything looked so good here. Had the pistachio lime zucchini cake, light and fluffy
I broke my daily ritual of fasting until noon coming to PureBread for the first time ! Yes, it is that good ! Lol
Servings are huge. We usually buy a couple and eat it over two days! Pretty spicy - sometimes the mild to mid seems a lot more on the hot side! Delicious - every single time.
Loved the chicken biryani. Will be back to try the roti. These guys don't mess around with spice level - the food is spicy!
Saag chicken, Madras, and butter chicken. I go there every week!
Friendly owners, delicious roti's and huge serving.
Vindaloo roti was fantastic. I crave it.
Delicious! Generous portions! Would definitely be back.
Quite spicy but really good, highly recommended.
I tried the saag paneer, and it was okay! Could be better though. Its way too hot (warm) though, don't burn your mouth - I did.
Roti are amazing and the staff are super friendly!
the baignan bhurta is delicious!
Great little space, service really depends on who you get
Great time was had but make sure you eat beforehand - food was overpriced especially because it really wasn't very good and there is barely anything to eat
The headliner was awesome. Good pub food too
Just wish the menu was more appetizing! Drink specials would also be nice:)
ah, hilarity ensued!
There's no food yet. March.2012.
If you are reading the tips below...there is a new Manager and staff since March 2013...so we hope you find our service 100% better and our beer and wine selection :) See you soon!
Decent selection of Gluten Free beers: 3 types of Greens, Estrella Damm Daura, Bards, St. Peter's and another I'd never seen before but can't remember the name...Service was good
Beer selection is good. Prices are mostly excellent for a private store, while American craft big bottles are comparable with places like Brewery Creek.
Very knowledgeable about wine: tasting notes from memory and always quick with a food pairing suggestion. You're on your own for liquors and beer though.
Definitely more about the wines than ales. Decent selection but why is the same stuff warm as cold? If you wanna talk beer go to Brewery Creek and talk to Chester
Excellent selection of local beers, pricy
Great beer selection and very helpful staff.
Great selection. Guy who works there seems like a dick. Female staff are nice!
Very poor service, the guy that works there is a jerk. Try the fruli beer, so good!!!!
Aces tasting tastless after 3 bottles....
Hidden gem. Quiet, cozy, great place to work or just think. Has those leave an anonymous story boxes. Highly recommended. $6 for a delicious crepe, salad and big coffee.
Strawberry dark chocolate crepe was awesome! Crepe was a chewy texture and cooked just right. Cappuccino was decent :) super cute decor and chill music.
Get a Nutella cr√™pe, some jasmine tea, seat back, relax & enjoy their playlist of jazz divas (Ella Fitzgerald, Carla Bruni,...)
This is such a great hidden gem. Great place to work because no one knows about it yet!
Quiet, great crepes and tea. Perfect place to relax, read a book or study.

try the chocolate banana scone.

An awesome alternative bookstore!
A trip to Vancouver isn't complete without a trip here for a banned books nerd!
Great place for supplies, books...and ALL the tickets for everything in Vancouver!!
What a great bookstore... Close to home
